Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getAllLayers(25.10)                                        getAllLayers(25.10)

Name
       getAllLayers  - Returns a complete list of all layers and floorplan ob-
       ject settings

Syntax
       getAllLayers

       [-help]

       [{object display multi internal module metal color custom oaLayout}]

       Returns a complete list of all layers and floorplan object settings. If
       you specify type, the software returns all the layers of the  specified
       type. This command can be used at any stage in the design flow.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each getAllLayers parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

               man getAllLayers

       {object display multi internal module metal color custom oaLayout}
              Specifies  the type of the layer. Innovus supports nine types of
              layers, which can be specified as follows:

              * object: Returns object layers,  which  represent  db  objects,
                such as instances, modules, pins, and so on.

              * display:  Returns  display-only or view-only layers, including
                flightlines, rulers, and congestion.

              * multi: Returns multiple color layers, such as  congestion  and
                yield maps.

              * internal: Returns internal layers, such as bump layers, struc-
                tured data path layers, etc.

              * module:  Returns  module  layers,  which are layers associated
                with hinsts.

              * metal: Returns wire/via layers, including metal/via, pin,  and
                blockage.

              * color: Returns color layers.

              * custom:  Returns  custom  layers,  which are used to represent
                custom objects and GDSII data.

              * oaLayout: Returns oaLayout layers.

              Data_type: enum, optional

Example
       Returns all metal layer names:

       getAllLayers metal

